                    "company": "International Criminal Court",
                    "description": "I conducted legal research for counsels and aided in the drafting of submissions on issues of public international law, international criminal law, and international humanitarian law relating to ongoing proceedings before all chambers of the Court. As part of the OPCV team legally representating victims, I have researched issues and aided in the preparation of submissions in proceedings relating to multiple cases, namely: Alfred Yekatom and Patrice-Edouard Nga\u00efssona; Bl\u00e9 Goud\u00e9; Bosco Ntaganda; Dominic Ongwen; Situation in Palestine; and Situation on Registered Vessels of Comoros, the Hellenic Republic and Cambodia.\n\nIn relation to the aforesaid proceedings I also prepared research dossiers on numerous issues, inter alia, statehood, territorial jurisdiction, reparations, United Nations law, status of former child soldiers, standards of evidence, and fair trial standards.\n\nI had also produced a detailed research and briefing dossier on the Situation in Myanmar/Bangladesh which included the history of the situation in Rakhine, the culture, and the legal and evidentiary issues relating to the alleged atrocities in Rakhine, Myanmar.",
